{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"DeviceOrientationEvent()","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent/DeviceOrientationEvent","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"<ol><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Device_orientation_events\">Device orientation events</a></strong></li><li><strong><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent\"><code>DeviceOrientationEvent</code></a></strong></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Constructor</summary><ol><li><em><code>DeviceOrientationEvent()</code></em></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent/absolute\"><code>absolute</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent/alpha\"><code>alpha</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent/beta\"><code>beta</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent/gamma\"><code>gamma</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance:</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event\"><code>Event</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Device Orientation Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEvent\"><code>DeviceMotionEvent</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventAcceleration\"><code>DeviceMotionEventAcceleration</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceMotionEventRotationRate\"><code>DeviceMotionEventRotationRate</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>The <strong><code>DeviceOrientationEvent()</code></strong> constructor creates a new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent\"><code>DeviceOrientationEvent</code></a> object.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: js-nolint notranslate\">new DeviceOrientationEvent(type)\nnew DeviceOrientationEvent(type, options)\n</pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"type\"><code>type</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>\n      A string with the name of the event.\n      It is case-sensitive and browsers set it to <code>deviceorientation</code> or <code>deviceorientationabsolute</code>.\n      In the latter case, <code>options.absolute</code> is always <code>true</code>.\n    </p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"options\"><code>options</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>An object that, <em>in addition of the properties defined in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event/Event\" title=\"Event()\"><code>Event()</code></a></em>, can have the following properties:</p>\n    <dl>\n      <dt id=\"alpha\"><code>alpha</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A number representing the motion of the device around the z axis,\n          expressed in degrees with values ranging from 0 to 360.\n          It defaults to <code>null</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"beta\"><code>beta</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A number representing the motion of the device around the x axis,\n          expressed in degrees with values ranging from -180 to 180.\n          This represents a front to back motion of the device.\n          It defaults to <code>null</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"gamma\"><code>gamma</code> <span class=\"badge inline optional\">Optional</span></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A number representing the motion of the device around the y axis,\n          expressed in degrees with values ranging from -90 to 90.\n          This represents a left to right motion of the device.\n          It defaults to <code>null</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n      <dt id=\"absolute\"><code>absolute</code></dt>\n      <dd>\n        <p>\n          A boolean value that indicates whether or not the device is providing orientation data absolutely.\n          It defaults to <code>false</code>.\n        </p>\n      </dd>\n    </dl>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":false,"content":"<p>A new <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent\"><code>DeviceOrientationEvent</code></a> object.</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/deviceorientation/#dom-deviceorientationevent-deviceorientationevent","title":"DeviceOrientation Event Specification"}],"query":"api.DeviceOrientationEvent.DeviceOrientationEvent"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.DeviceOrientationEvent.DeviceOrientationEvent","dataURL":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/DeviceOrientationEvent/DeviceOrientationEvent/bcd.json"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Return value","id":"return_value"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"}],"summary":"The DeviceOrientationEvent() constructor creates a new DeviceOrientationEvent object.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-09-13T05:21:27.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/deviceorientationevent/deviceorientationevent","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/api/deviceorientationevent/deviceorientationevent/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/da88b2f3a23b9d93f083003f13c06f9d96073f6a","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology 